      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RONALDO VELLA (2) could not have been more impressive last start in his a brilliant 35.49 win at Richmond over 622m. Has the ability and expected to go close again. ZIPPING EVANIA (6) could manage only third last time but ran respectable time (29.74) at Wentworth Park over 520m when beaten 5 lengths in a Grade 4/5. Should be in this for a long way. STOP AND STARE (1) was always well back but did hit the line strongly late to finish 4th and beaten only 2 lengths (29.81) at Wentworth Park. Form is hard to fault from this box, with a win and two minor placings from three starts. Deserves plenty of respect. ASHBY GNOCCHI (5) placed last time in impressive time - worth considering.",
